            "answer_text": "Yes two obtuse angles can be adjacent. For example: in a hexagon the sum of all 6 angles is 720 degrees.In a hexagon having equal length of all sides ( a regular hexagon), all angles are also equal.Hence the value of each angle is 720/6=120 degrees.Which is an obtuse angle. Hence 2 obtuse angles can be adjacent. ",
